{"cursor":"9786","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\nAn 'intervention' is an orchestrated attempt by one or many people –\nusually family and friends – to get someone to seek professional help with\nan addiction or some kind of traumatic event or crisis, or other serious\nproblem. The term intervention is most often used when the traumatic event\ninvolves addiction to drugs or other items. Intervention can also refer to the\nact of using a similar technique within a therapy session.\n\nInterventions have been used to address serious personal problems, including,\nbut not limited to, alcoholism, compulsive gambling, drug abuse, compulsive\neating and other eating disorders, self harm and being the victim of abuse.\n\n","linknr":183,"url":"Therapeutic_intervention","recorded":1362508922,"links":35,"instances":["the_office","us_tv_channel","how_i_met_your_mother","columnist","psychological"],"pdf":["http://www.recoveryconnection.org/intervention-guide/InterventionGuide.pdf"],"categories":["Addiction","Counseling"],"headings":["Direct and indirect interventions","Plans for direct intervention","Prior preparation","Controversy","Civil liberty problems with forcible intervention","In popular culture","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["traumatic_event","psychological"],["bravo","us_tv_channel"],["mike_walker","columnist"],["intervention","how_i_met_your_mother"],["michael_scott","the_office"]],"members":["michael_scott","bravo","intervention","mike_walker","traumatic_event"],"related":["Traumatic_event_(psychological)","Crisis","Substance_dependence","Alcoholism","Compulsive_gambling","Drug_abuse","Eating_diso